## 📜 Code of Conduct

This project and everyone participating in it is governed by our commitment to providing a welcoming and inspiring community for all. Please be respectful and constructive in your interactions.

## 🤝 How Can I Contribute?

### 🐛 Reporting Bugs

Before creating bug reports, please check [existing issues](../../issues) to avoid duplicates. When you create a bug report, include as many details as possible using our [bug report template](.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/issue_report.yaml).

**To report a bug:**

1. Go to the [Issues](../../issues) tab
2. Click "New Issue"
3. Select "🐛 Bug Report"
4. Fill out the template in your preferred language (English, Español, or Galego)

**Good bug reports include:**

- **Clear title** - Describe the issue concisely
- **Steps to reproduce** - Detailed steps so others can replicate the issue
- **Expected behavior** - What you expected to happen
- **Actual behavior** - What actually happened
- **Environment details** - OS, browser, app version
- **Screenshots/logs** - Visual evidence or error messages if applicable
- **Severity level** - How critical is this issue?

**Example:**

> **Title:** [BUG]: App crashes when saving item with special characters
>
> **Steps:**
> 1. Open the app
> 2. Create a new item with title "Test & Example"
> 3. Click save
> 4. App crashes
>
> **Expected:** Item should be saved successfully
>
> **Actual:** App crashes with error "Invalid character"
>
> **Environment:** iOS 16.5, Things v1.2.0

### ✨ Suggesting Features

Feature suggestions are welcome! Please use our [feature request template](.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_request.yaml) to ensure we have all the information needed.

**To suggest a feature:**

1. Go to the [Issues](../../issues) tab
2. Click "New Issue"
3. Select "✨ Feature Request"
4. Fill out the template in your preferred language (English, Español, or Galego)

**Good feature requests include:**

- **Problem statement** - What problem does this solve?
- **Proposed solution** - How would you like this to work?
- **Alternatives considered** - What other solutions did you think about?
- **Priority level** - How important is this to you?
- **Use cases** - Who would benefit from this feature?
- **Additional context** - Screenshots, mockups, or examples

**Example:**

> **Title:** [FEATURE]: Add tags to organize items
>
> **Problem:** I have many items and it's hard to find related ones
>
> **Solution:** Add a tagging system where users can create custom tags and filter items by tags
>
> **Alternatives:** Categories or folders, but tags are more flexible
>
> **Priority:** High - would greatly improve organization
>
> **Use case:** Students organizing study materials, professionals managing projects

### 💻 Contributing Code

Want to contribute code? That's awesome! 

**This repository is for project-wide issues and discussions only.** For code contributions, please refer to the specific repository you want to contribute to:

- **[Frontend](https://github.com/LLEIDAHACKERS/things-frontend)** - Mobile application
- **[Extension](https://github.com/LLEIDAHACKERS/things-extension)** - Browser extension  
- **[Backend](https://github.com/LLEIDAHACKERS/things-backend)** - API and services

Each repository has its own CONTRIBUTING guide with:
- Setup instructions
- Development workflow
- Commit guidelines
- Pull request process
- Code style guidelines
- Testing requirements

**General workflow:**

1. Find or create an issue in this central repository
2. Comment on the issue to let others know you're working on it
3. Go to the specific repository (frontend/backend/extension)
4. Follow that repository's CONTRIBUTING guide
5. Reference the issue number from this repository in your PR

## 🌿 Branching Strategy

All Things repositories follow the same branching model:

```
main
 └── develop
      ├── feat/branch-name or feat/issue-id
      └── fix/branch-name or fix/issue-id
```

### Branch Types

- **`main`** - Production-ready code. Protected branch, only accepts merges from `develop`
- **`develop`** - Integration branch for features. All development happens here first
- **`feat/*`** - New features (e.g., `feat/user-authentication` or `feat/123`)
- **`fix/*`** - Bug fixes (e.g., `fix/login-crash` or `fix/456`)

### Naming Conventions

**Option 1: Descriptive name**
```bash
git checkout -b feat/dark-mode
git checkout -b fix/memory-leak
```

**Option 2: Issue ID**
```bash
git checkout -b feat/123
git checkout -b fix/456
```

**Option 3: Combined**
```bash
git checkout -b feat/123-dark-mode
git checkout -b fix/456-memory-leak
```

### Workflow Example

```bash
# Start from develop
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop

# Create your feature branch
git checkout -b feat/123-add-tags

# Make your changes and commit
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add tagging system"

# Push to your fork
git push origin feat/123-add-tags

# Create PR to develop branch (not main!)
```

**Important:** Always create PRs targeting the `develop` branch, never directly to `main`.

## 🏗️ Repository Structure

Things is organized into three main repositories:

- **[things-frontend](https://github.com/LLEIDAHACKERS/things-frontend)** - Mobile application (iOS/Android)
- **[things-extension](https://github.com/LLEIDAHACKERS/things-extension)** - Browser extension (Chrome/Firefox/Safari)
- **[things-backend](https://github.com/LLEIDAHACKERS/things-backend)** - API and backend services

**This repository** serves as the central hub for:
- Project-wide issues and bug reports
- Feature requests that span multiple components
- General discussions and questions
- Project roadmap and planning
- Documentation

## 💬 Getting Help

- **Questions?** Open a [Discussion](../../discussions)
- **Bug found?** Create a [Bug Report](../../issues/new/choose)
- **Feature idea?** Submit a [Feature Request](../../issues/new/choose)
- **Need clarification?** Comment on existing issues

## 🙏 Thank You!

Your contributions, whether reporting bugs, suggesting features, or writing code, make a real difference. We appreciate your time and effort in helping make Things better for everyone.

